 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.1.3","title":"Obsidian: readiness, compliance, verification, and operator guidance","description":"Finish Obsidian with readiness and doctor outputs, vault-path remediation guidance, deterministic tests across note and attachment workflows, and explicit V3 compliance evidence for a local knowledge-base connector.","acceptance_criteria":"- closeout requires comprehensive deterministic unit coverage for auth, timeout, retry, error-mapping, pagination or state transitions, and the highest-risk provider-specific mutations\n- closeout requires archetype-appropriate integration coverage built on shared `fcp-testkit` helpers rather than connector-local one-offs\n- closeout requires at least one replayable E2E or host-backed verification script that runs through `rch`, captures detailed structured logs, and preserves manifest, readiness, doctor, and conformance artifacts\n- operator guidance must name prerequisites, dedicated environments, redaction rules, common remediation paths, and rerun commands for the verification bundle\n- evidence attached to the bead must be sufficient for a future agent to rerun verification without reopening external planning notes","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:14:40.329231Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-03-18T06:28:29.341072Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.1.3","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:14:40.329231Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.1.3","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18T01:14:40.329231Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.5.1.3","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-j05nu.9.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18